 History                                                            37 1451     
 ----------                                                         37 1451     
 This library was produced by the Low Energy Interactions Physics   37 1451     
 (LEIP) group at North Carolina State University.  Twelve           37 1451     
 temperatures are available in this library.  The inelastic         37 1451     
 scattering cross section libraries for H in CH2 (Polyethylene)     37 1451     
 were developed using molecular dynamics methods [1,2]. This        37 1451     
 material is a polymer.  The incoherent elastic cross section is    37 1451     
 significant, so the MT = 2 section for elastic scattering is       37 1451     
 present. The LEAPR module from NJOY2012 code system was used       37 1451     
 to produce MT = 2 and MT = 4 data.  By convention, MAT=37 and      37 1451     
 ZA=137 are used for H in Polyethylene.                             37 1451     
                                                                    37 1451     
